%section#about
  %p
    This project is based on the <a href="http://darowski.com/hall-of-wwar">Hall of wWAR</a>, an alternate Hall of Fame populated by a single statistic.
    That statistic, <strong>weighted Wins Above Replacement</strong> (or <strong>wWAR</strong>), combines the value of all aspects of a playerâ€™s contributions (hitting, pitching,
    fielding, baserunning, position, etc.) and gives additional adjustments for peak performance, playoff heroics, and season length.
    Read more <a href="http://darowski.com/hall-of-wwar">about wWAR</a> for more information.
  %p
    The Red Sox Hall of wWAR takes the same approach, but instead re-populates the <a href="http://boston.redsox.mlb.com/bos/history/feature_hall_of_fame.jsp">Red Sox Hall of Fame</a>. There are 56 players in the Red Sox Hall of Fame. 

